  "created_by": "Mark Atwood",
  "description": "Implement the social layer: favourites, boosts, follows, and the timeline queries that pull it together. The home timeline is a SQL read query — no fanout, no cache. Thread context reconstruction (ancestors/descendants) has historically been buggy across implementations; test it explicitly with nested threads.",
